  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Upper Nile State Eye care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of this project is to increase eye services coverage by strengthening the health system and building the capacities of the communities to take responsibility over their own eye health. The aim is to develop eye health/care services , establish a secondary eye care facility at Malakal Teaching Hospital, increase access to eye care services and strengthen eye disease control programmes to tackle cataract and trachoma in the short term and childhood blindness, refractive errors and low vision in the medium term. Targets; For 2013, the project envisage that a total of 2,500 people will benefit from TT surgeries while 172,323 persons will benefit from antibiotic treatment in two counties of the state. About 500 cataract sufferers will receive surgery. 
This will result in (outcome):
- Increased access to eye care services
- Reduced blinding trachoma infection
- Restored sight for trichiasis sufferers
- Health system strengthened and Malakal eye unit would offer secondary eye care services</narrative>
  </description>
